{
  "abstract": "Haulms from four groundnut cultivars (ICGV 02266, 86564, 91114, and 00440) were compared with Co4 grass (+100 g concentrate) fresh and as silage (+200 g concentrate measuring voluntary feed intake, digestibility and growth over 43 days in 6 groups of Nellore rams with six animals per group (28.37+kg)… Organ1c matter 1ntakc and average daily weight changes were significantly (P<0.05) higher in ramson pure groundnut haulms compared to those on either supplemented Co4 fresh grassor silage…",
